name: Grossglockner 2
description:
One of the most popular attractions in Austria is the Grossglockner High Alpine road. At nearly 50km, this mountain path cuts through the heart of the Hohe Tauern, and is one of the most breathtaking routes in Europe. The road concludes at Grossglockner, the highest peak in the Austrian alps and the origin of The Pasterze glacier. 

I was fortunate enough to spend some time photographing this unforgettable route, the product of which includes the photographs I am presenting in this collection.
